OL,5, Sir Lindsay Hoyle has led tributes to  
OL,6, his father, the former Labour MP and   
OL,7, "truly dedicated parliamentarian" Doug 
OL,8, Hoyle, who has died aged 98.           
OL,10,FThe veteran politician was MP for      
OL,11,FNelson and Colne from 1974 and 1979 and
OL,12,Ffor Warrington from 1981 to 1997 before
OL,13,Fbeing ennobled as Lord Hoyle.          
OL,15,FAnnouncing his father's death, the     
OL,16,FCommons Speaker said he had been "a    
OL,17,Fforce to be reckoned with".            
OL,19,FLabour leader Sir Keir Starmer said he 
OL,20,Fhad been "a tenacious campaigner".     
